
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-jain-nvo3-vxlan-ping-00.txt'>
    <title>"Detecting VXLAN Segment Failure", Pradeep Jain, Kanwar Singh, Florin Balus, Wim Henderickx, Vinay Bannai</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-jain-nvo3-vxlan-ping-00.txt</link>
    <description>This proposal describes a mechanism that can be used to detect Data Path Failures and sanity of VXLAN Control and Data Plane for a given VXLAN Segment.  This document defines the following:  o  Information carried in a VXLAN "Echo Request", and  o  "Echo Reply" for the purposes of fault detection and isolation, and mechanisms for reliably sending the Echo Request and reply.</description>
    <dc:date>2013-06-06T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
